('420R', 'SDS', '006509', 'UG', 'Critical Encounter with Human Nature', 'This course explores human nature, issues fundamental to human life, and theories which have developed around these issues. The approach is interdisciplinary and intercultural/interreligious with emphasis on such themes as self knowledge, community, loneliness and anxiety, free will and purpose in human life, and the nature of human happiness.', 'Prereq: Level at least 3A', 'No Consent Required', 'No Consent Required', NULL),
