('284', 'RS', '008331', 'UG', 'Gender and the Great Religions', 'Through a review of the teachings of the great religious traditions about gender, this course aims to arrive at a global view of the situation of beliefs and practices related to gender "in the world of religion". It will examine the role of religion as an important influence on gender and human development. [Note: This course fulfils an Area 3 requirement for Religious Studies majors.]', 'Antireq: WS 261', 'No Consent Required', 'No Consent Required', NULL),
