('121', 'CIVE', '010660', 'UG', 'Computational Methods', 'Introduction to computer programming, examples of efficient numerical algorithms for basic scientific computations. Programming and problem solving concepts introduced in the course will be incorporated into group projects involving civil, environmental, or geological engineering applications. The language of instruction will be Matlab. [Offered as: CIVE 121 (W), ENVE 121 (S), GEOE 121 (S)]', 'Prereq: Level at least 1B Civil Engineering. Antireq: CHE 121, ECE 150, MTE 121/GENE 121,  SYDE 121', 'Department Consent Required', 'Department Consent Required', NULL),
