('343', 'FINE', '013514', 'UG', 'Topics in Fine Arts Experiential Learning', 'This course enables Fine Arts students to gain valuable work experience within an art-related environment. Collaboration between students, professional artists, and art institutions creates a unique learning experience that complements the student''s program of study. [Note: Course will be graded on a CR/NCR basis. A minor field trip fee may apply. This is a repeatable course, subject to different content; it may be completed a total of two times.]', 'Prereq: Level at least 3A Fine Arts majors', 'No Consent Required', 'No Consent Required', NULL),
('344', 'FINE', '013515', 'UG', 'Fine Arts Internship', 'This experiential learning course is intended to enable Fine Arts students to gain valuable work experience within an art related environment. The course is designed to complement the student''s academic program by providing an opportunity for the practical application of skills and concepts. [Note: Course will be graded on a CR/NCR basis. A minor field trip fee may apply.]', 'Prereq: FINE 343; Fine Arts majors', 'No Consent Required', 'No Consent Required', NULL),
('402', 'FINE', '013519', 'UG', 'Directed Study', 'This course is intended to help Fine Arts students make the transition from art school to professional practice by providing an opportunity to examine their own practice within the larger context of the professional art world. [Note: A field trip fee of $100 may be required.]', 'Prereq: Level at least 4A Fine Arts students', 'No Consent Required', 'No Consent Required', NULL),
