('826A', 'PSYCH', '015946', 'GRD', 'Research Practicum in Developmental Science l', 'Research in developmental psychology is comprised of a wide array of methods, analyses, and approaches. Researchers able to effectively use this diverse toolkit are better positioned to solve important problems in developmental psychology. The goal of this practicum is to provide students with novel experiences conducting research in developmental psychology or a complementary interdisciplinary area to their research. To this end, contingent on the availability of appropriate opportunities, students will work in a laboratory outside that of their primary research advisor
